🧩 Core Concept: Page-Centric Dashboard
Each client can:

🔓 Activate a Page using its Page ID

📋 View a list of their activated Pages

🔁 Switch between Pages

🧠 Build or manage flows per Page

🖼️ Suggested UI Layout
🏠 Dashboard Home
Once a Page is activated, show:

✅ Active Page ID

🧠 Flow summary or preview

🔁 “Switch Page” button

➕ “Activate New Page” button

📋 Page List View
Let users see all their activated Page IDs:

Show as cards or a simple list

Each card has:

Page ID

Optional name or label

“Open” button

“Remove” or “Deactivate” option


🔧 Backend Structure (Firebase)
Firestore Example:
plaintext
users/
  [userId]/
    pages: [pageId1, pageId2, pageId3]

pages/
  [pageId]/
    name: "My Chat Page"
    flowData: {...}
    createdAt: timestamp
You can store the user’s activated Page IDs locally (e.g., in localStorage) or associate them with a user account if login is supported.

⚙️ Activation Logic
When user enters a Page ID:
Check if it exists in pages/

If valid, add to their local list

Load the flow for that Page

🧠 Flow Management Per Page
Once a Page is active:

Show flow builder or chat interface

Save all flow data under that Page ID

Allow editing, saving, and previewing

🧪 Optional Features
🔍 Search for Page ID

🏷️ Add custom labels to Pages

📤 Export or share Page flow

🔐 PIN protection for sensitive Pages

